On Topic: As for YouTubers I watch consistently:
  • Mumbo Jumbo: College student and full-time YouTuber who makes Minecraft videos. He's part of the Hermitcraft group and has awesome redstone videos.
  • Game Theory: Nerdy videos with math and science that relate to video gaming. My fav ;D
  • Vsauce/Vsauce3: Scientific-related channels. Really awesome content in general. I haven't checked out Vsauce2, if that even exists ._.
  • danisnotonfire/AmazingPhil: The only vloggers I watch
  • DanAndPhilGames: These guys ^ play games.
That's about all I can think of for now...
